35:12.811 --> 35:15.846
any mystery why I'm on
the lookout for grandma?

35:15.847 --> 35:17.582
Anybody's grandmother's
would do.

35:17.583 --> 35:21.819
I've been known to hitch-hike
highways looking for any

35:21.820 --> 35:23.688
grannies and given my fragile

35:23.689 --> 35:26.090
emotional sense it makes sense

35:26.091 --> 35:30.728
that I would dragoon Tomaso's

35:30.729 --> 35:33.898
mom into making me a lunch.

35:33.899 --> 35:36.534
Is that intriguing or sad?

35:36.535 --> 35:39.937
Smells good in here.

35:39.938 --> 35:40.206
Cheers.

35:40.207 --> 35:41.207
Cheers.

35:41.208 --> 35:43.341
Need any help chopping parsley?

35:43.342 --> 35:45.876
Oh, perfect.

35:45.877 --> 35:47.212
For lunch we've got the shrimp

35:47.213 --> 35:49.780
and sardines from earlier at the

35:49.781 --> 35:51.949
market, but first this.

35:51.950 --> 35:53.351
Just grab one?

35:53.352 --> 36:01.352
It's like arancini but with
hole owed out potatoes.

36:01.627 --> 36:07.598
Basically, and with
all the cheese.

36:07.599 --> 36:12.570
And deep in and sealed the
potatoes and then fried.

36:12.571 --> 36:19.644
My mother cooks for
everybody, even if it was

36:19.645 --> 36:21.612
so when we have to share all

36:21.613 --> 36:22.780
together and have a dinner, my

36:22.781 --> 36:25.783
mother is cooking for everybody.

36:25.784 --> 36:27.718
Because the problem is when she

36:27.719 --> 36:30.120
cook, even if she know it's only

36:30.121 --> 36:32.156
for five people, she
cooking for ten.

36:32.157 --> 36:40.157
Just in case.

36:43.502 --> 36:45.069
This is Sicily, after all.

36:45.070 --> 36:46.504
This is the classic starter.

36:46.505 --> 36:48.573
Also a bread and tomato salad.

36:48.574 --> 36:50.875
Would you like to try something?

36:50.876 --> 36:57.982
That's old school.

36:57.983 --> 36:59.984
We use bread that a harder.

36:59.985 --> 37:02.320
We usually do bread
that is two days old.

37:02.321 --> 37:03.454
It's really good.

37:03.455 --> 37:08.359
Really, really good.

37:08.360 --> 37:08.927
That's Sicily right there.

37:08.927 --> 37:09.194
Right.

37:09.195 --> 37:15.533
Yes.

37:15.534 --> 37:18.536
Fresh shrimp sautes
in butter and garlic.

37:18.537 --> 37:23.007
When they are confronted
with the shrimp, fry away.

37:23.008 --> 37:29.046
That's the way you see
if it's fresh or not.

37:29.047 --> 37:30.981
So typical day, when you were

37:30.982 --> 37:37.488
15 years old what did
you eat for lunch?

37:37.489 --> 37:40.391
Fish and pasta.

37:40.392 --> 37:41.492
Basically you have to go right

37:41.493 --> 37:44.795
behind the corner to
find your products.

37:44.796 --> 37:46.964
Whatever we could produce in

37:46.965 --> 37:49.400
Zitly, that's what
we choose to buy.

37:49.401 --> 37:50.235
Watch this.

37:50.236 --> 37:51.536
Zip the bone right out.

37:51.537 --> 37:52.203
Out comes all the bone.

37:52.204 --> 37:55.506
Who needs a knife?

37:55.507 --> 38:03.507
Sardines fileted neatly,
sauteed in garlic and oil.

38:07.819 --> 38:12.857
I'll tell you, another two hours

38:12.858 --> 38:14.825
here I'll be speaking Sicilian.

38:14.826 --> 38:15.327
You have to eat it hot.

38:15.328 --> 38:17.428
This is very nice.

38:17.429 --> 38:25.429
If you don't like this,
there's no hope for you.

38:29.508 --> 38:30.409
If you like it.

38:30.409 --> 38:30.909
Tell her.

38:30.910 --> 38:33.511
Happy.

38:33.512 --> 38:34.380
This is a delicious meal.

38:34.381 --> 38:36.747
And to eat in this beautiful

38:36.748 --> 38:40.919
home with some really
good home cooked food.

38:53.031 --> 38:58.135
>My last night in Sicily.

38:58.136 --> 38:59.770
After this I'm calling in bed

38:59.771 --> 39:02.407
