But I'm not barking or shrieking

39:08.980 --> 39:12.817
with my pants wrapped around my

39:12.818 --> 39:14.151
head which is what my instincts

39:14.152 --> 39:15.953
are telling me I
should be doing.

39:15.954 --> 39:19.156
One of life's great
joys is cheese.

39:19.157 --> 39:20.825
No, I'm eating cheese.

39:20.826 --> 39:22.993
Which makes me happy.

39:22.994 --> 39:23.294
Always.

39:23.295 --> 39:25.295
And drink wine.

39:25.296 --> 39:26.664
Good wine.

39:26.665 --> 39:28.833
And a hell of a lot of it.

39:28.834 --> 39:31.669
I'll make it over the hump
with any luck at all.

39:31.670 --> 39:39.670
We have a mozzarella
here, a pepperccino.

39:49.087 --> 39:51.689
Tori joins me for a final meal.

39:51.690 --> 39:53.424
This is not a concept that

39:53.425 --> 39:55.826
exists in America, but it is a

39:55.827 --> 39:57.361
concept that should exist.

39:57.362 --> 40:02.099
Okay, now please
explain what it is.

40:02.100 --> 40:05.836
A hotel linked to the territory.

40:05.837 --> 40:13.644
Use local product, local recipe.

40:13.645 --> 40:18.048
Penne, sun dried tomatoes
all from the farm.

40:18.049 --> 40:26.049
Oh, man that looks good.

40:27.793 --> 40:30.828
Wow.

40:30.829 --> 40:33.163
Fantastic.

40:33.164 --> 40:36.200
Some nice olive oil
also from the farm.

40:36.201 --> 40:36.468
More wine.

40:36.469 --> 40:41.472
I might just make it.

40:41.473 --> 40:45.375
This is called agridolce.

40:45.376 --> 40:46.410
It's bitter.

40:46.411 --> 40:49.747
If you talk about Italy, it is

40:49.748 --> 40:54.351
the most interesting
part of Italian cuisine.

40:54.352 --> 40:55.385
Life is too good.

40:55.386 --> 40:57.655
I need a little bitterness to

40:57.656 --> 40:58.823
remind myself of the internal

40:58.824 --> 41:01.158
tragedy of our existence.

41:01.159 --> 41:04.662
The sweet and sour of the life.

41:04.663 --> 41:07.498
One final attempt before I go

41:07.499 --> 41:08.333
to extract something meaningful

41:08.334 --> 41:11.201
on what it means to be Sicilian.

